programme.title: Batman Returns
programme.desc: Gotham City faces two monstrous criminal menaces: the bizarre, sinister Penguin and the slinky, mysterious Catwoman. Can Batman battle two formidable foes at once? Especially when one wants to be mayor and the other is romantically attracted to Bruce Wayne?

programme.title: Star Trek Nemesis
programme.desc: Captain Jean-Luc Picard and the Enterprise crew find themselves on a diplomatic mission to initiate peace with the Romulans. But upon arrival on the alien planet, the crew is faced with a threat that could lead to Earth's destruction and Picard meets his most dangerous adversary yet, a surprisingly personal nemesis.

programme.title: Sudden Impact
programme.desc: A victim of a savage rape exacts revenge on her aggressors in Clint Eastwood's fourth Dirty Harry movie. Considered to be the darkest, dirtiest and most violent one in the series.

programme.title: Saving Private Ryan
programme.desc: Seen through the eyes of a squad of American soldiers, the story begins with Wold War II's historic D-Day invasion, and then moves beyond the beach as the men embark on a dangerous special mission. Captain John Miller must take his men behind enemy lines to find Private James Ryan, whose three brothers have been killed in combat. Faced with impossible odds, the men question their orders. Why are eight men risking their lives to save just one? Surrounded by the brutal realities of war, each man searched for his own answer - and the strength to triumph over an uncertain future with honour, decency and courage.

programme.title: Lawrence of Arabia
programme.desc: When T.E. Lawrence was attached to the British general staff in Arabia, he inspired the feuding Arabian chieftains to rebel against the Turks, leading to the birth of the Arabian kingdom.

programme.title: Meatballs
programme.desc: The wackiest head counsellor in North Star camp history, Tripper Harrison devotes his summer activities to cracking jokes, chasing female staffers, and plotting the demise of their evil rich rivals, the snotty young brats at nearby Camp Mohawk. Jam-packed with hysterical off-the-wall hjinks, drop-dead gorgeous babes in the woods and the riotous one-liners, Meatballs is an "Animal House goes to summer camp".

programme.title: Groundhog Day
programme.desc: Bill Murray is at his wry, wisecracking best in this riotous romantic comedy about a weatherman caught in a personal time warp on the worst day of his life. Teamed with a relentlessly cheerful producer and a smart-aleck cameraman, TV weatherman Phil Connors is sent to Punxsutawney, Pennsylvania, to cover the annual Groundhog Day festivities. But on his way out of town, Phil is caught in a giant blizzard, which he failed to predict, and finds himself stuck in small-town hell. Just when things couldn't get any worse, they do. Phil wakes the next morning to find it is Groundhog Day all over again and again and again.

programme.title: Pet Sematary
programme.desc: With the title track sung by the Ramones fright meister Stephen King directs this chilling tale about a magical Indian burial ground. When his three-year-old son is killed on the road outside his home, Dr Louis Creed begins to think about the stories surrounding the ancient cemetery and how those buried there can be resurrected.

programme.title: Cujo
programme.desc: Based on a Stephen King novel, Cujo is a happy St. Bernard until he is bitten on the nose by a rabid bat and slowly begins manifesting the symptoms of his fatal illness. His condition deteriorates as he attacks people again and again, until finally, mum Donna Trenton and her son Tad are trapped inside the family car with Cujo lurking nearby, set to kill them any way he can. A showdown is inevitable.

programme.title: The Big Chill
programme.desc: Celebrate good friends as they reunite for the funeral of a college pal. During the weekend that follows, these friends compare their '60s ideas with the harsh reality of their lives in the '80s, and discover that in a cold world, you need your friends to keep you warm.

programme.title: Look Who's Talking Too
programme.desc: Mikey the wisecracking tot acquires a baby sister with the same wry sense of humor. Meanwhile their parents have emerged out of wedded bliss to face some real-life issues involving money problems and a gun-toting relative. Mikey is also learning how to use the toilet for the first time.

programme.title: The Money Pit
programme.desc: Walter and Anna believe they've arrived 'home sweet home' when they buy the house of their dreams. But life quickly becomes a nightmare as their dilapidated mansion falls apart around them, and they struggle to stay together even as they slide further into the money pit. It's outrageous entertainment for anyone who's ever been deeply in love or deeply in debt or both.

programme.title: Wildcats
programme.desc: As the daughter of a legendary grid iron star, a young woman's greatest desire is to coach a team of her own. But when the chauvinistic powers-that-be assign her to an inner-city ghetto school, the spirited female has her work cut out for her.

programme.title: Police Academy
programme.desc: As a crime wave sweeps the city and the police department suffers a shortage of officers, the mayor decrees that admission to the Police Academy will be open to any and all applicants. Now the first cadets, a collection of oddballs, eccentrics and misfits will soon be let loose on the streets. That is if they somehow manage to graduate in this worldwide hit comedy that started the series of Police Academy films.

programme.title: Ghostbusters
programme.desc: A trio of university parapsychologists lose their research grant and decide to open their own business, Ghostbusters, and almost at once are summoned to investigate the strange happenings in a Central Park West apartment. What they discover is that all Manhattan is being besieged by otherworldly demons.

programme.title: Back To The Future III
programme.desc: Marty McFly ends up in the wild west of 1885 to save mad scientist Doc Brown from a crazed gunfighter.

programme.title: The Goonies
programme.desc: Following a mysterious treasure map into a spectacular underground realm of twisting passages, outrageous booby-traps and a long-lost pirate ship full of golden doubloons, the kids race to stay one step ahead of a family of bumbling bad guys and a mild mannered monster with a face only a mother could love.

programme.title: Uncle Buck
programme.desc: An idle, good-natured bachelor, Uncle Buck is the last person you would think of to watch the kids. However, during a family crisis, he is suddenly left in charge of his nephew and nieces. Unaccustomed to suburban life, fun-loving Uncle Buck soon charms his younger relatives Miles and Maizy with his hefty cooking and his new way of doing the laundry. His carefree style does not impress everyone though, especially his rebellious teenage niece, Tia, and his impatient girlfriend, Chanice. With a little bit of luck and a lot of love, Uncle Buck manages to surprise everyone.

programme.title: Planes, Trains & Automobiles
programme.desc: Businessman Neal is dying to get home for Thanksgiving and loud-mouthed Del, a shower curtain ring salesman is driving him nuts. Will they reach Chicago without killing each other?

programme.title: Blues Brothers 2000
programme.desc: Elwood, after serving his time in prison, finds he is now the lone 'Blues Brother' and is once again enlisted by Sister Mary Stigmata in her latest crusade to raise funds for a children's hospital. Once again hitting the road to re-unite the band for the New Orleans Battle of the Bands, Elwood is pursued cross-country in yet another colossal car chase, led by Cabel the Curtis' son, the Russian Mafia, and a militia group. This time, Elwood has the help of a young orphan, and a strip club bartender.

programme.title: Lethal Weapon 4
programme.desc: With personal crises and age weighing in on them, LAPD officers Riggs and Murtaugh must contend with a deadly Chinese crime lord trying to get his brother out of prison.

programme.title: Almost Famous
programme.desc: A high-school boy in the early 1970s is given the chance to write a story for Rolling Stone magazine about an up-and-coming rock band as he accompanies them on their concert tour.

programme.title: Batman & Robin
programme.desc: Cryogenic scientist gone wrong, Mr Freeze wants to turn Gotham City into a frozen wasteland. Poison Ivy has revenge on her mind after a toxic run-in with a Wayne Enterprises scientist. While she has designs on Mr Freeze, his cold heart is consumed only by his demented plans. With the addition of Batgirl, the dynamic duo becomes a trio. Will Gotham survive?

programme.title: Tootsie
programme.desc: Michael Dorsey is a talented actor, but his demanding nature and stubborn temperament have antagonised every producer in New York. Now his agent insists no one will hire him. But Michael needs money, eight thousand dollars to be exact, and to earn it, he's willing to play the role of a lifetime. This out-of-work actor finds success, love and frustration when he gets the role of his life playing a woman.

programme.title: Better Off Dead
programme.desc: After his girlfriend ditches him for a boorish ski jock, Lane decides that suicide is the only answer. However, his increasingly inept attempts bring him only more agony and embarrassment.

programme.title: The Breakfast Club
programme.desc: When Saturday detention started, they were the Jock, the Princess, the Brain, the Criminal, and the Basket Case, but by that afternoon they had become closer than any of them could have imagined.

programme.title: Scrooged
programme.desc: This surreal update of the Charles Dickens classic has a mean-spirited TV executive haunted into the Christmas spirit by three special time-travellers.

programme.title: Trapped in the Farmhouse
programme.desc: A woman on the run from her abusive boyfriend seeks shelter from a terrifying storm in an isolated farmhouse, unaware that something far worse is waiting for her inside.

programme.title: Christmas Hotel
programme.desc: Erin grew up in the small town of Mt Holly but always dreamt of living in a big city. Her first job - working the desk at the Mt Holly Inn - started her on a path to New York where she now works at the prestigious Windsor Hotel. When her boss tells her she will receive a promotion if she can pull off a big project, she is thrilled - until she realises the project is in her hometown. Erin returns home to discover that the locals don't appreciate their precious Mt. Holly Inn being bought out by a big corporation. And heading up the charge? Erin's ex-boyfriend Conner. But when several hotel staff members come down with the flu, Erin is forced to enlist Conner's help with hotel's Christmas events. As they two re-establish their relationship, Erin has to figure out if what she really wants is a promotion or to be home again.

programme.title: Murdaugh Murders: Part 1
programme.desc: Alex Murdoch's family's hidden crimes begin piling up as he attempts to conceal his own financial felonies but falls into a dark spiral.

programme.title: An Amish Sin
programme.desc: Inspired by a true story, the movie follows Rachel, an Amish teen who refuses to obey her parents command that she marry the man who abused her as a child. When she attempts to run away, she is caught and sent to a neighbouring rehab for Amish girls who do not follow the rules. Managing to escape from the facility, she makes her way to a city where she must learn to live and find her place in our world.

programme.title: One Night Stand Murder
programme.desc: Alyssa wakes up in a home that's not hers and discovers a dead body. With no memory of how she got there and no idea of who the body belongs to, Alyssa tries to piece together what happened the night before.

programme.title: Lonely Crime Fanatic
programme.desc: Sparks fly when a lonely true crime fan meets her favourite podcast host, but things soon turn strange as his fascination with her turns into obsession.

programme.title: The Lover in the Attic: A True Story
programme.desc: This is the lurid, true story about femme fatale Dolly, her murdered husband, and her lover, Otto - the man in the attic. In the 1930s, Dolly met and seduced her repairman Otto. But she was already married to successful business man Fred. Their affair grew so strong that she decided to move him into her attic and keep him as her sex slave, unbeknownst to Fred. Otto lived in Dolly's attic for four years, even moving houses with them, until one night during a heated argument between Dolly and Fred, Otto burst downstairs from the attic and killed Fred. Now the two must cover up the murder and try to live a normal life, but will they be able to keep their secret?

programme.title: A Model Murder
programme.desc: Model Kara Woods begins to get disturbing messages from one of her fans, causing her to seek help from a security influencer. Things are fine until Kara's stalker shows up in person.

programme.title: Ann Rule's A Murder To Remember
programme.desc: Inspired by Ann Rule's true crime collection Empty Promises. Javier and Robin Rivera are celebrating their one-year anniversary on a camping trip. But when Javier ends up dead, Robin finds herself alone in the rough wilderness. She accepts help from another camper, a mysterious stranger named Sam and slowly places her life in his hands. But is Sam there to protect Robin? Or does she need protecting from him?

programme.title: No One Would Tell
programme.desc: Laura Collins (Shannen Doherty), single mum to daughter Sarah (Matreya Scarrwener), has had a history of rocky relationships, so when Sarah begins dating the popular and charismatic Rob Tennison (Callan Potter), Laura is thrilled with what she sees. But when it becomes increasingly clear that Rob has a darker, possessive side, Laura lives in a state of denial about her daughter's relationship until Sarah goes missing. Laura must find the will to fight for justice for Sarah when a case against Rob is brought to trial and presided over by a powerful judge (Mira Sorvino).

programme.title: V.C. Andrews' Hidden Jewel
programme.desc: Ruby's struggle continues to find a happy life with Beau Andreas, the true father of Pearl, and to protect their precious daughter. Sheltered from sorrow, innocent young Pearl thrives in the sunshine of a loving home, except for the haunting nightmares of her earliest years and the dark family secrets she worries will one day shadow her destiny. As Pearl's journey and dreams of success swirl away with the hurricane winds, and she journeys to the swamps in search of her mother and the shocking truths of her heritage. In the warm embrace of a gentle Cajun man, she discovers a blessed refuge. But, until the storm clouds clear, Pearl cannot savour the springtime sweetness that always seems beyond tomorrow.

programme.title: V.C. Andrews' All That Glitters
programme.desc: Driven from the Dumas Mansion back to her beloved bayou, Ruby is determined to make a secure and happy home for her precious infant daughter, Pearl. Paul Tate, her first love, is at her side once more with dazzling wealth. Whisking her into his grand house, it seems their future is assured. But the thick, expensive walls of Cypress Woods cannot shut out the terrible memories and shocking reasons that have woven their fabric over her destiny, or the cold eyes of Paul's mother, Gladys, reminding Ruby of the secret she must keep to give Pearl a loving father. Desperate to find the complete, fulfilling life she craves, Ruby builds a precarious new existence, a flimsy shanty of hope that the first flood washes away. Only when the storm exposes the very blackest evils of the past will she glimpse the rainbow's fragile promise, a morning of sunshine and laughter with a family of her own.

programme.title: Abducted on Prom Night
programme.desc: Against her better judgement, a recently-divorced mother allows her troubled daughter to attend prom, but what was supposed to be the best night of their lives, turns into a twisted game of cat-and-mouse as the daughter and her friends are taken hostage by their limousine driver, who has a sinister connection to her family.

programme.title: Liz & Dick
programme.desc: A chronicle of the fiery, legendary, on-again off-again romance between Hollywood stars Elizabeth Taylor and Richard Burton.

programme.title: And Baby Will Fall
programme.desc: Expectant parents become prime suspects in the disappearance of a pregnant woman who was last seen at their garage sale.

programme.title: The Night Before Christmas
programme.desc: An estranged mother and daughter are caught in a snowstorm on Christmas Eve and are forced to take refuge inside a church. They meet a handsome pastor and a music teacher who motivate them to reconnect.

programme.title: My Father's Murder in Greece
programme.desc: When Allie's father George takes her on a celebratory trip to Greece to discover her familial roots, George is murdered. Allie must uncover family secrets to bring the killer to justice.

programme.title: Escaping the Madhouse: Nellie Bly Story
programme.desc: On a mission to expose the deplorable conditions and mistreatment of patients at the notorious Women's Lunatic Asylum, investigative reporter Nellie Bly feigns mental illness in order to be institutionalized to report from the inside. The movie delivers an intense and fictionalized account of actual events surrounding Nellie's stay beginning after Nellie has undergone treatment, leaving her with no recollection of how she came to the asylum or her real identity. Nellie's unwillingness to submit to authority results in unspeakable torture at the hands of the head nurse, Matron Grady. When Nellie captures the attention of Dr Josiah who tries to help her, Grady's barbaric tactics only intensify, leading Nellie to question if she actually does belong in the asylum after all. Nellie Bly's expose was the first of its kind in America and inspired the global reformation of mental health care.

programme.title: The Killing Game
programme.desc: Ten years after her daughter's murder, Eve is contacted by a man claiming to be the child's killer, who taunts her with mysterious clues and threats to kill again. Based on the novel by Iris Johansen.

programme.title: Buried in Barstow
programme.desc: Hazel King is a single mother determined to protect her daughter from the life she once had while defending and protecting those who can't protect themselves.

programme.title: Secrets In The Desert
programme.desc: While on a road trip through the desert, Charlie and her boyfriend Aidan break down in the middle of nowhere. While Aidan waits for a tow truck, Charlie heads to a nearby diner to find help. When Aidan goes missing, Charlie finds herself stranded in a strange town unsure who to trust. The only thing she knows is she might just be their only chance to get out alive.

programme.title: Heaven Sent
programme.desc: As Christmas approaches, a humble prayer ascends into the depths of space: Maire Taylor, a smart, beautiful businesswoman asks that her husband find the strength and wisdom to let go of their 9 year marriage. While simultaneously a second prayer comes from Billy Taylor, a hopelessly romantic artist asking that his wife receive the strength and wisdom to hold on. From these humble pleas comes an answer in the form of a little miracle - an 8-year-old runaway from heaven - who takes it upon herself to rekindle the once intimate friendship and romance that has slowly, but surely slipped away from Billy and Maire due to a heart-wrenching loss.

programme.title: V.C. Andrews' Heaven
programme.desc: Based on the novel by V.C. Andrews. Of all the poor people living in "the willies" - the foothills of the mountains of West Virginia, the Casteels were considered lowest. Yet, the eldest daughter, Heaven Leigh Casteel, was still the prettiest and smartest girl in the backwoods, despite her ragged clothes and dirty face. Heaven encouraged her four younger siblings to cling to their pride and hope for a day that they'd escape their poverty and show the world what decent, talented children they were. But when Heaven's stepmother runs away, Luke, her irresponsible drunkard of a father, decides to give away his children one by one, tearing her family apart. Heaven is sent off to live in the home of Luke's deranged ex-lover, Kitty. There, she is subjected to more torment but finds solace in the arms of her stepfather Cal, as they begin a taboo relationship.

programme.title: V.C. Andrews' Dark Angel
programme.desc: Based on the novel Dark Angel, the second book in the "Casteel" family series by V.C. Andrews. In her grandmother's fine, rich, Boston house, Heaven Casteel dreams of a wonderful new life of new friends, the best schools, beautiful clothes and most importantly, love. The pearls of culture, wisdom and breeding will now be hers. Soon she will make the Casteel name respectable, find her brothers and sisters and have a family again. But even in the world of the wealthy, there are strange forebodings, secrets best forgotten. And as Heaven reaches out for love, she is slowly ensnared in a sinister web of cruel deceits and hidden passions.

programme.title: Christmas Reservations
programme.desc: It's Christmas at the Treeline Ski Resort, where Holly plans every event and keeps all the guests happy. When her college sweetheart checks in, Holly discovers she has her own reservations about life and love.

programme.title: I Was Lorena Bobbitt
programme.desc: It's been 26 years, but everyone still knows the notorious case of Lorena Bobbitt. But what's gotten lost in the countless tabloid headlines and tasteless jokes that followed was the story of a severely abused young woman whose torment, both physical and mental, at the hands of her husband pushed her over the edge. In this Lifetime Original movie, Lorena tells her story, and we follow her journey from a wide-eyed, immigrant bride to a battered wife, and an unlikely media sensation, with her ultimately emerging as a strong, thoughtful woman who has devoted her life to advocating for other abused women.

programme.title: Hunt for the Labyrinth Killer
programme.desc: An ace ADA works with a driven cop to catch Daedalus, a serial killer infamous for luring his victims to their deaths with elaborate traps.

programme.title: I'll Be Watching
programme.desc: Based on the novel The Purple Rose by Christi R. Walsh. After narrowly escaping the clutches of a deadly stalker, a beautiful young woman flees to a remote anonymous town, where she rebuilds her life and finds the man of her dreams, until the man of her nightmares tracks her down.

programme.title: A Nurse to Die For
programme.desc: A father hires a live in nurse to help care for his sick daughter. However, as she suffers a series of setbacks, he starts to wonder if the nurse might actually be the one keeping her sick.

programme.title: Nightmare School Moms
programme.desc: Two mothers battle to see which of their overachieving daughters will be accepted to a prestigious university. However, when one of their methods quickly spirals out of control, the games turn deadly.

programme.title: He Loves Me
programme.desc: Desperate to save her idyllic life and marriage, Laura's mysterious past begins to emerge, and with it paranoid delusions that pose a serious threat to anyone who gets in her way.

programme.title: The Christmas Consultant
programme.desc: A workaholic mother gets more than she bargained for when she hires a sought after consultant to help her and her family through the holidays.

programme.title: My Dog's Christmas Miracle
programme.desc: A new relationship between a single dad and a woman with a devoted but demanding Maltese terrier may end before it begins as the jealous dog and the man's young son work to sabotage the budding romance.

programme.title: Heaven Sent
programme.desc: As Christmas approaches, a humble prayer ascends into the depths of space: Maire Taylor, a smart, beautiful businesswoman asks that her husband find the strength and wisdom to let go of their 9 year marriage. While simultaneously a second prayer comes from Billy Taylor, a hopelessly romantic artist asking that his wife receive the strength and wisdom to hold on. From these humble pleas comes an answer in the form of a little miracle - an 8-year-old runaway from heaven - who takes it upon herself to rekindle the once intimate friendship and romance that has slowly, but surely slipped away from Billy and Maire due to a heart-wrenching loss.

programme.title: The Christmas Pact
programme.desc: Can best friends fall in love? That's the question next door neighbours Sadie and Ben will answer as they keep the spirit of Christmas and the magic of their childhood pact alive! When they were eight years old, they planted a scrawny 3-foot tall Christmas tree behind their church and the Christmas Pact began. But as life gets in the way the pact is threatened to be broken. Ben and Sadie need some Christmas Magic to recommit to each other and promise to keep their special holiday traditions. With each Christmas that passes by, Ben and Sadie's Christmas tree grows taller and stronger; and so does their love. The pact bearing fruit to the magic of Christmas and the undeniable answer. Yes, friends can fall in love! love!

programme.title: A Country Christmas Story
programme.desc: A starry-eyed young girl journeys from the mountains of Appalachia to the stage at Dollywood, where she discovers the impact of African Americans on the world of country music.

programme.title: Cyberstalker
programme.desc: Thirteen years ago, Aiden's world was torn apart after an online stalker followed her into the real world and broke into her home to claim the object of his desire. The resulting night of terror ended with the murders of both Aiden's mother and father. The stalker escaped the scene without Aiden seeing his face; he is gone without a trace, an unknown man, a murderer now watching Aiden's every move. To escape this danger Aiden spends the next 13 years offline, in therapy and secluded anonymity. Who should Aiden trust in a web of deception where no one may be who they seem? There is nowhere for Aiden to hide when someone wants to love her to death. Mischa Barton, Dan Levy and Ron Lea star. (2012)

programme.title: My Christmas Prince
programme.desc: A teacher returns to her home town, where she is joined by her boyfriend and learns that he is the crown prince of Madelvia.

programme.title: V.C. Andrews' Fallen Hearts
programme.desc: Based on the novel Fallen Hearts, the third book in the "Casteel" family series by V.C. Andrews. As her childhood sweetheart's bride, Heaven would savour now the love she had sought for so long. And free from her father's clutches, she would live again in her backwoods town, a respected teacher and cherished wife. But after a wedding trip to Boston's Farthinggale Manor and a lavish, elegant party, Heaven and Logan are persuaded to stay, lured by Tony Tatterton's guile to live amidst the Tatterton wealth and privilege. Then the ghosts of Heaven's past rise up once more, writhing around her fragile happiness, threatening her precious new life with scandal.

programme.title: V.C. Andrews' Gates Of Paradise
programme.desc: Based on the novel Gates of Paradise, the fourth book in the "Casteel" family series by V.C. Andrews. The car crash that killed Heaven and Logan left Annie Casteel Stonewall orphaned and crippled. Whisked off to Farthinggale Manor by the possessive Tony Tatterton, Annie pines for her lost family, but especially for Luke, her half-brother. Friend of her childhood, her fantasy prince, her loving confidante without the warm glow of Luke's love, she is lost in the shadows of despair. When Annie discovers Troy's cottage hidden in Farthinggale's woods, the mystery of her past deepens. And even as she yearns to see Luke again, her hopes and dreams are darkened by the sinister Casteel spell. Treacherous, powerful and evil!

programme.title: Big Driver
programme.desc: A mystery writer stranded on a stretch of New England road is offered assistance by another driver. She quickly discovers her saviour is actually her assailant - and a killer. From best-selling author Stephen King.

programme.title: V.C Andrews' Ruby
programme.desc: In the heart of the bayou, Ruby Landry lives a simple, happy life. The only family Ruby Landry has ever known are her loving guardian, Grandmere Catherine, a Cajun spiritual healer, and her drunken, outcast Grandpere Jack. Her life is filled with hope and promise, especially when her attraction for handsome Paul Tate blossoms into a mysterious, wonderful love. But Paul's wealthy parents forbid him to associate with a poor Landry while Grandmere urges her to follow her dream of becoming a great painter. In a faded photograph, Ruby glimpses for the first time the image of her father and learns of a shameful deception and a shocking scheme of blackmail that now must come to light. Stunned by these revelations, she is devastated when Grandmere dies, leaving her to seek out her father in his vast New Orleans mansion. There, in a house of lies, madness, and cruel torment, Ruby clings to her memories of Paul to keep her heart alive. For only their love can save her now.

programme.title: Happy Face Killer
programme.desc: Grisly serial killer Keith Hunter Jesperson taunts authorities with scribbled confessions bearing a smiley face at the scenes of his crimes. Based on a true story.

programme.title: The Inherited
programme.desc: Eve's happily-ever-after with the man of her dreams becomes a waking nightmare after they move into the house willed to him by his first wife, who died under horrific circumstances.

programme.title: Deadly Secrets By the Lake
programme.desc: This whodunit murder mystery uncovers the secrets kept by the idyllic lakeside town of Thornwood Heights. It tells the story of the prodigal daughter who returns home to prove her sister's innocence of murder but is met by a lost, forbidden love, dark family secrets and a long standing family rivalry fuelled by the disappearance of a childhood best friend.

programme.title: Kidnapping in the Grand Canyon
programme.desc: When two best friends hiking the Grand Canyon trust an experienced hiking guide to bring them on an off trail adventure, things go south when he takes them captive, and they have to fight both man and nature to make it out.

programme.title: Secrets In The Desert
programme.desc: While on a road trip through the desert, Charlie and her boyfriend Aidan break down in the middle of nowhere. While Aidan waits for a tow truck, Charlie heads to a nearby diner to find help. When Aidan goes missing, Charlie finds herself stranded in a strange town unsure who to trust. The only thing she knows is she might just be their only chance to get out alive.

programme.title: Harry and Meghan: Escaping the Palace
programme.desc: The couple decide to step back from the duties of the British monarchy following the birth of their son Archie.
